<br>
This Thursday night at 6pm PST (that's 7 mountain, 8 central, and 9 eastern), I'll take anyone level 10 and up to the Oasis of Marr.  Good and evil both can attend this one.  I'm not sure what the closest bind point is -- it may be Freeport (for good characters, Nektulos for evil?), but traveling is fairly safe.  If anyone dies, I'll gate back and SoW.<br>
<br>
There's a lot of stuff in the Oasis of Marr.  Some scary stuff -- Sand Giants, Drybone skellies -- but more importantly, lots and lots of crocodiles.  <br>
<br>
Crocodiles don't drop much in the way of loot, unfortunately, but they're VERY good experience.  They come in a lot of flavors -- caiman, crocodile, deepwater caiman, and deepwater croc, in ascending order of toughness.  There's also the occasional mummy or desert madman.<br>
<br>
Oasis tactics are a bit different from Derv/Orc camps or Crushbone.  It's a big, open zone with a lot of stuff running around.  You have to watch your back at all times.  The best way I've found to hunt there with a group is to designate a puller, who runs off and drags monsters back to a stationary group.  <br>
<br>
When something really scary comes by, the group can run to a safe area and wait for it to leave.  A lot of very high level characters hang around there killing the really scary stuff for xp, so chances are someone will be there to help anyway.<br>
<br>
I'm taking Hama's suggestion and trying this on a Thursday instead.  That's a work night for me, so I can't get on any earlier than 6pm Eastern.<br>
<br>
We can meet at the West Gate of Freeport.  I'll show up there at 6pm and SoW everyone who wants to go.  If you want to go, email me at gwion_the_druid@hotmail.com or post here.<br>
<br>
